wilescollection.config.title: WilE's Collection Config
block.wilescollection.crafting_table.hel:
A Crafting Table with two rows of inventory, recipe collision resolver, quick selection of last used recipes, and small crafting tweaks:
Mouse-scroll over the output slot to increase/decrease the item count in the crafting grid. Shift-click items distributes equally in the crafting grid. Ctrl-shift moves all stacks between inventories. Click the output slot with an item to automatically search and select the first possible recipe.
block.wilescollection.crate.help: A simple crate that keeps its inventory when being relocated. It shows the item placed into the bottom-left Item Frame slot.

block.wilescollection.fluid_barrel.help: Wooden Barrel storing up to 12 buckets of liquid.
block.wilescollection.ladder.help: Ladder with a really good grip. Look up or down to climb faster.
item.wilescollection.ariadne_coal.help: Draws orientation arrows. The arrow direction depends on where you click the block.
item.wilescollection.charged_lapis.help: Stores one Experience level. Consume to retrieve the XP, this also removes all active effects. Created with a Mind Squeezer.
item.wilescollection.charged_lapis_squee: Creates Charged Lapis from Lapis Lazuli in your inventory by draining XP levels. It will hurt a bit. The Charged Lapis can be consumed again.
Hmm, it doesn't work, not enough XP left?
item.wilescollection.crushed_copper.help: Can be faster smelted to copper ingots.
item.wilescollection.crushed_gold.help: Can be faster smelted to gold ingots.
item.wilescollection.crushed_iron.help: Can be faster smelted to iron ingots.
item.wilescollection.crushing_hammer.hel: Manually crushing ore in a crafting table increases the ore yield. Low durability, cannot be repaired, no attack damage. Hit animals and villagers to gently push them, hard knock back for monsters.
item.wilescollection.peculiar_ring.help: Toss it on top of an Anvil and drop Lapis Lazuli on it to charge up armor and tool repair.
item.wilescollection.tracking_compass.he:
Helps to find friends and
 locations again. Click a block
 or entity with the device to
 track it. The built-in compass
 will then show the way. When you
 are close, the compass also
 points up or down. When the
 target is not in your dimension
 or died, it will rotate 180
 degrees (the 'dot' position).
 To clear the current target,
 click straight down on the ground.
item.wilescollection.tracking_compass.hi: First click on the ground below you to clear the current tracking target.
